sentence: Home improvement warehouse operator The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) on Wednesday saw its earnings estimates raised by analysts at Jefferies & Co.
The firm maintained its "Buy" rating and $36 price target on HD, which implies a 14% upside to the stock's Tuesday closing price of $31.71.
For 2011, Jefferies boosted its profit estimate for the company from $1.90 per share on $7.17 billion in revenue to $1.97 per share on $7.26 billion in revenue.
For 2012, the analyst lifted its estimates from $2.20 per share on $7.62 billion in revenue to $2.28 on $7.75 billion.
The only risk the firm sees for Home Deport is the possibility of housing prices remaining low, but noted it expects EPS growth in the future.
"Management raised EPS guidance, which along with an 8% FCF yield on our FY12 estimates, should support the share price at this level," said a Jefferies analyst.
Shares of Home Depot ( HD ) have a 2.96% dividend yield, based on last night's closing stock price of $31.71.
The stock has technical support in the $28-$30 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $34 price level.
We would remain on the sidelines for now.
